===Etymology===
From {{enm}}, from {{ang}} [[niht]]. Cognates include {{grc}} [[νύξ]] (nyx), {{la}} [[nox]], {{got}} [[𐌽𐌰𐌷𐍄𐍃]] (nahts), {{de}} [[Nacht]], {{ru}} [[ночь]] (noch').
===Pronunciation===
*nīt, /naɪt/, /<tt>naIt</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[knight]], [[nite]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aɪt|Rhymes: -aɪt]]

===Alternate spellings===
*[[nite]] (''informal'')

===Noun===
'''night''' (''Plural:'' [[nights]])

#the period between [[sunset]] and [[sunrise]], when the sky is dark.
#(''countable'') [[darkness]].
#:''The cat disappeared into the night.''

